# SM-102 mRNA Lipid Nanoparticle — SBOL3 Example

A structured SBOL3 representation of a four-component ionisable lipid 
nanoparticle for mRNA delivery, based on publicly available FDA filings 
and supporting technical literature for the Moderna mRNA-1273 formulation.

## Files

- `design.ttl` — SBOL3 Turtle representation of the formulation

## Formulation

| Component | Role | Molar fraction |
|---|---|---|
| SM-102 | Ionisable lipid | 0.50 |
| DSPC | Helper lipid | 0.10 |
| Cholesterol | Membrane modulator | 0.385 |
| DMG-PEG2000 | Surface stabilisation | 0.015 |
| mRNA payload | Active cargo | — |

Molar ratio sum (lipid phase): 0.50 + 0.10 + 0.385 + 0.015 = 1.000

## Modelling notes

Conventions used in `design.ttl` are documented in 
[docs/data-model.md](../../docs/data-model.md).

## Source

Based on publicly available FDA filings and supporting technical literature 
for the Moderna mRNA-1273 COVID-19 vaccine.
